<div id="review_45764219" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/45764219" />
    <a title="Clodagh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/224448-clodagh"><img alt="Clodagh" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/45764219?book_show_action=true">Feb 08, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Clodagh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Clodagh" href="/user/show/224448-clodagh">Clodagh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer45764219" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8898880881191174945">The Butcher Boy is one of those amazing books that you hope won&apos;t end. I read other reviews in which people said that it is depressing, and yes it is if you look at the plot outline of a mentally disturbed boy who doesn&apos;t have the best of luck. However there is a lot of dark humour in it that has you giggling despite yourself. The plot is dark, there are some very disturbing issues like Paedophilia, suicide etc... but by showing it through the eyes of a mad boy these topics are not touched in a </span>
  <span id="freeText8898880881191174945" style="display:none">The Butcher Boy is one of those amazing books that you hope won't end. I read other reviews in which people said that it is depressing, and yes it is if you look at the plot outline of a mentally disturbed boy who doesn't have the best of luck. However there is a lot of dark humour in it that has you giggling despite yourself. The plot is dark, there are some very disturbing issues like Paedophilia, suicide etc... but by showing it through the eyes of a mad boy these topics are not touched in a serious manner, you can happily read through giggling at the genius of Patrick McCabe. I would recommend it to anyone who does not get shocked easily and has good imagination and a dark sense of humour.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8898880881191174945" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


