<div id="review_323107729" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/323107729" />
    <a title="J.J. Toner" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5474402-j-j-toner"><img alt="J.J. Toner" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1530976604p2/5474402.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/323107729?book_show_action=true">May 03, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J.J. Toner" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J.J. Toner" href="/user/show/5474402-j-j-toner">J.J. Toner</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780330328746" href="/book/show/1056734.The_Butcher_Boy">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer323107729" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13523016329522867563">This is a truly wonderful book. I read it in less than two days, devouring every word, dissecting the prose to extract the factual from the imagined from the dialogue. This was easy for me, although I can see how it might be difficult for readers not so familiar with Irish idiom (and the comic books of the sixties).<br/><br/>Other reviewers spoke about the violence in the book, but there is hardly any, and what there is occurs close to the end and is treated in a characteristically off-hand way.<br/><br/>I loved it</span>
  <span id="freeText13523016329522867563" style="display:none">This is a truly wonderful book. I read it in less than two days, devouring every word, dissecting the prose to extract the factual from the imagined from the dialogue. This was easy for me, although I can see how it might be difficult for readers not so familiar with Irish idiom (and the comic books of the sixties).<br /><br />Other reviewers spoke about the violence in the book, but there is hardly any, and what there is occurs close to the end and is treated in a characteristically off-hand way.<br /><br />I loved it. I loved the way everything in Francie's life was shown through his distorted perspective and yet could be seen by the reader with crystal precision.<br /><br />The book is a superb achievement, a shining example of what can be accomplished with words by a supreme artist.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13523016329522867563" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


